        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 4:58PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Kim, or 39 miles southwest of Springfield, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Baca
and southeastern Las Animas Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
